This paper is about session-based recommender systems, which are a type of recommendation system that focuses on predicting the next item a user will interact with based on their current session. This topic is closely related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG), as well as artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and social and information networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper discusses various methods for modeling item features and session-level dependencies, which are relevant to natural language processing and computational linguistics (cs.CL).
